1. cargo init for making new cargo file in a manual project.
2. cargo new project_name :- used for new project with cargo build in it. 
3. cargo is a package manager for rust programming language.
4. rustc main.rs or file name :- gives you an executable file for the same project. ( but gcc/gcc+ must be installed - build essentials.)
5. cargo check :- for checking the program without any executable file.
6. cargo build :- gives you an executable file - ./target/debug/program_name
7. rust uses snake_case strictly or gives you an error if not used correctly.
8. cargo run :- directly gives you the executable file and run the program with code check.
9. Programming is set of instructions :- always remember.
10. If you do not want to make a git repo under the new cargo repo then :- cargo new project_name --vcs none
 learnt mutability and immutability, variables and data types.
